node.text:
A more sustainable, environmentally conscious future is all of our responsibility 🌍🌊

Since I learned about my own carbon footprint, I discovered that it has never been easier to measure your climate impact, educate yourself and take steps to align with climate positive initiatives, leaders and companies.

@panerai is a brand I have loved and respected for as long as I can remember (loads of you have commented on the watches I wear 😎🙏) and I am proud to lend my voice to the amazing work they are doing through the #PaneraiEcologico project and the innovation they are bringing to the industry.

This short video is the start of some exciting #PaneraiWW21 projects pushing the boundaries of watch-making and educating people on sustainable consumption #WatchesandWonders2021 

Lots more coming 😉 @panerai #panerai

node.text:
Last year @piawurtzbach and I said goodbye to each other in New York, she was heading to Asia for work and I was heading to the Middle East. The day of her flight I had terrible food poisoning and couldn’t take her to the airport but we’d made a plan to meet back in the US in two weeks....

It was the last time we saw each other face to face for almost 6 months. 

Every day we were apart we would FaceTime, me starting my day in New York, her ending her day in Manila. Sometimes we’d speak for hours, sometimes a few minutes and at some point during lockdown she started sending me the lyrics of songs and then singing them to me when we spoke. This song always made me smile 😊 

It’s these small, thoughtful things that you never see publicly but define the person she is and even though you don’t need one day a year to tell someone important you love them, I thought it was appropriate that on Valentine’s Day after such a crazy year, I let her know how much I love her and how much I care about the small things she does 😊Happy Valentine’s Day baby 😘

node.title: A few days after Valentine’s Day

One of the most vibrant and exciting industries in the world, responsible for trillions of dollars of economic value and countless life changing experiences... I LOVE this industry and love inspiring people to follow their passion and get into travel. 

I had a chance to talk with my Greek family @katerinakatopis & @marketinggreece about why the industry is so important, why the Greek tourism offering is so special and what tourism marketers need to do to get themselves back to growth. 

We cover the ethos behind @beautifuldestinations, my optimism for sustainable tourism, the magic of Greece and its people and why content marketing is so critical in the recovery of our industry. 

It’s always an honour for me to share my thoughts on business & our industry so a huge thank you to my Greek friends and to anyone that watches this 🙏

node.text: Massive thanks to @andymanteit & @turfgames for having me on the ‘Off The Turf’ Podcast to talk about health, fitness & performance. It’s the first time ever that I’ve done an interview about my performance habits sharing how I train, how I eat, how I recover and how it ties to business & travel 🦾🦿 I shared the things I do to optimize my sleep, my training volume, ideas on gut health & immunity, mitochondrial function, managing stress, meditation, hot/cold therapy, breath-work, mental health, nutrition/supplements and being an entrepreneur.  I touch on how I built @beautifuldestinations, the challenging times we’re all going through during COVID-19 and my passionate belief that travel is a force for good and ultimately, we’ll get through this 😉 The health space is my biggest passion and connecting with new audiences in elite sport & performance is something I love doing, so if you’re interested in hearing the whole podcast head over to @turfgames for the details or drop me a DM 🤙

node.text:
Front Rack KB Squats x 8
Hang Clean > Front Squat (3 sec pause) x 5
Single Arm Swing x 6/side
Goblet Squat  x 10
Push Up x 10
Weight Plate Reverse Lunge x 6/side
100 Single Unders 
The goal is to complete in under 3 minutes 👍 6 circuits with 1 minute rest after each circuit. Nasal only breathing - this dramatically increases the load on your body when you train :) New York is now under a stay at home order until May 15th, so I have a whole month to completely change my training & come up with something new! I’ll share the workouts over the coming weeks and as always DM me if you want more info. Stay home, stay healthy 😉 (🎵: “Breathe” Zeds Dead Remix, The Prodigy)

node.text: I’ve always wanted to share more training, nutrition and general wellness content so set a goal whilst we’re in quarantine to do exactly that 👍 Loads of people have reached out since I started sharing on stories, so here’s a really simple way to train all the major muscles of your upper body. I got this pull up/dips bar on amazon for $60 and it fits any standard width door, with my back pack I can increase the weight if needed & with the sports mask I’m wearing (and nasal breathing) can stress my cardiovascular system at the same time (it restricts oxygen intake simulating higher altitude training- more on this later). This sessions goal was to do 100 body weight dips (taking as many breaks as needed) then 50 weighted dips and 50 weighted pull ups (again as many breaks as needed). I’m working my chest, back, bi’s, tri’s and core and no matter your experience level you can adjust the reps, rest & additional weight to suit your ability. Simple & effective 😉 @tenthousand.cc @equinox @athleticgreens @oxygenadvantage (🎵 “Shipping Up To Boston” Dropkick Murphys from The Departed soundtrack 🇮🇪 🇺🇸)

node.text: Four of the things I enjoy most in life and subjects I could talk about all day :) I did this interview last year and was asked what were the hardest things I’d been through and what did I learn in the process. Seems trivial in light of what we’re facing now but the lessons I’ve learnt in travel- of respecting people, supporting one another, not judging others less fortunate or different to yourself hold true now more than ever. We’re all in for a tough few months, friends & colleagues in the travel industry especially but watching out for one another, being diligent with our health and restricting our travel plans is the only way to get through this. Things will be bad but we will bounce back 🤙

We still have a long way to go and can always be better but hope this talk will show some of our thinking around how to travel and have positive impact whilst protecting our environment 😊🤙🌏 @wwf @world_wildlife

node.text:
I have an amazing friend in Marrakech who owns a beautiful boutique hotel in the Palmeraie called @jnanetamsna. Its 24 rooms, 5 pools and stunning botanical gardens are a short trip away from the busyness of city life. I will always remember the time I spent there business planning, reading and switching off- it’s also one of the places we got content for @panerai that we used to launch our partnership in GQ 😉

If you have the chance to visit I promise you won’t regret it 🇲🇦 

📷: @nazihels
